    <h3>What is 3Guppies?</h3>
    <p>3Guppies let's you send photos from Facebook to any mobile phone &#150; FREE. 
    Add faces to your phonebook, make your own wallpaper, or surprise a friend with 
    a picture message! Stay tuned for more great features...</p>
    
    <h3>Is 3Guppies really free?</h3>
    <p>Yep, 3Guppies won't charge you a dime. You just need text messaging and 
    Internet access, and standard carrier charges for those services apply.</p>
    
    <h3>Will it work with my phone?</h3>
    <p>It should &#150; 3Guppies works with thousands of different phones on almost 
    every U.S. and Canadian carrier, including: Alltel, Aliant, Amp'd Mobile, AT&T, 
    Bell Mobility, Bluegrass Cellular, Cellular One, Centennial Wireless, Cincinnati Bell, 
    Cingular, Cricket, Edge, Einstein PCS, Epic PCS, Fido, Highland Cellular, 
    Metro PCS, MTS Mobility, Nextel (Hybrid), Plateau Wireless, Qwest, Rogers AT&T, 
    Sasktel Mobility, Sprint PCS, Suncom, T-Mobile, Verizon, West Central Wireless</p>
    
    <h3>Is it safe to give you my phone number?</h3>
    <p>Yes &#150; we'll keep it to ourselves. 3Guppies will never sell your personal info or 
    send you spam.</p>
    
    <h3>How do I download to my phone?</h3>
    <p>Most phones will receive a text message with a link in it. To click on the link select 
    Menus or Options and 'GO TO'. Your photo should download automatically &#150; Enjoy!</p>
    
    <blockquote>* Verizon customers will receive photos via an MMS message which means it 
    will be sent as a attachment just like an email. All you have to do is open and 
    save the attachment.</blockquote>
    
